<item>
            <title>[LU-19229] improved IR NID list handling on client side</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19229</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Imperative recovery can provide extended information about target NIDs for a client to use, but client has several restrictions preventing it from using that data&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;client uses for mount only config NIDs and fails early if can&apos;t initialise initial connection based on NIDs in config file, IR NIDs are not even tried in that case&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;client fails immediately if first NID in IR NID list is not suitable for new connection for some reason, without trying others&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;client fails to mount if IR provides more than 32 NIDs even if they all are good&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</description>
